// Explicit view: semantic errors + lints emerge as DIAG lines with positions
// translated to user-file coordinates (core region suppressed). Wire protocol:
//   DIAG <line> <col> <severity> <code> <slug> <note_count> <message>
//   NOTE <line> <col> <message>   × note_count
// The code (E0001/W0002) is stable forever; the slug ("undefined_symbol") is
// the diagnostic's human-readable identity; the message can evolve.
// RUN: %build/arche-analyzer --dump %s | grep -qF "error E0001 undefined_symbol 0 Undefined symbol 'unknown_thing'"
// RUN: %build/arche-analyzer --dump %s | grep -qF "warning W0002 proc_no_effect 0 proc 'noop'"
// Error carries the offending expression's position (the name token).
// RUN: %build/arche-analyzer --dump %s 2>/dev/null | grep -qxE "^DIAG 12 [0-9]+ error E0001 undefined_symbol 0 Undefined symbol 'unknown_thing'"
entry :: system {
  x := unknown_thing;
}
noop :: proc() {
}

#run entry
